DESCRIPTION:THIS AGREEMENT PROVIDE FUNDS TO THE RECIPIENT TO CONDUCT (1) SITE CHARACTERIZATION ACTIVITIES AT POTENTIAL OR CONFIRMED HAZARDOUS WASTE SITES; (2) UNDERTAKE RESPONSE PLANNING AT SITES ON THE NATIONAL PRIORITIES LIST (NPL) AND (3) ACTIVITIES WHICH ARE NOT ASSIGNABLE TO SPECIFIC SITES THAT SUPPORT THE RECIPIENT'S SUPERFUND PROGRAM.ACTIVITIES:PRE-REMEDIAL ACTIVITIES ARE NECESSARY TO IDENTIFY CONTAMINATED PROPERTIES OR SITES WHERE ACCIDENTAL OR INTENTIONAL RELEASES HAVE OCCURRED, AND TO DETERMINE IF REMEDIAL ACTION UNDER CERCLA IS WARRANTED TO PROTECT HUMAN HEALTH AND THE ENVIRONMENT. PRE-REMEDIAL ACTIVITIES ARE A CRITICAL COMPONENT OF THE MPCA AS THEY PROVIDE THE ONLY REGULATORY MECHANISM IN NEW MEXICO TO INVESTIGATE CASES OF ENVIRONMENTAL CONTAMINATION THAT ARE LACKING ANY KNOWN POTENTIALLY RESPONSIBLE PARTIES. PRE-REMEDIAL ACTIVITIES ENSURE THAT HAZARDOUS WASTE SITES WITH HUMAN EXPOSURES ARE CONTROLLED, AND THE MIGRATION OF CONTAMINATED GROUNDWATER OR SOIL VAPOR IS CONTROLLED.

MANAGEMENT ASSISTANCE ACTIVITIES SUPPORT EPA AND NMED GOALS TO PRESERVE AND RESTORE THE ENVIRONMENT BY USING INNOVATIVE WASTE MANAGEMENT PRACTICES AND CLEANING UP CONTAMINATED PROPERTIES TO REDUCE RISKS POSED BY RELEASES OF HARMFUL SUBSTANCES. MANAGEMENT ASSISTANCE ACTIVITIES WILL CONTRIBUTE TO CONTROLLING RISKS TO HUMAN HEALTH AND THE ENVIRONMENT BY ENSURING THAT SELECTED REMEDIES ADDRESS AND MITIGATE THE IMPACT OF ACCIDENTAL OR INTENTIONAL RELEASES AND CLEAN UP AND RESTORE CONTAMINATED SITES OR PROPERTIES TO APPROPRIATE CLEAN UP LEVELS. NMED WILL EVALUATE PROPOSED AND IMPLEMENTED REMEDIES TO ENSURE THAT CONTAMINATED SITES DO NOT POSE THREATS TO HUMAN HEALTH AND THE ENVIRONMENT AND ALLOW FOR THE REUSE OF THE LAND. NMED WILL PARTICIPATE, ASSIST OR LEAD IN FINAL SITE ASSESSMENT DECISIONS, CONSTRUCTION COMPLETION ACTIVITIES, AND EVALUATION AND SELECTION OF FINAL REMEDIES AND CLEANUP GOALS TO ENSURE THAT HUMAN EXPOSURE TO SUPERFUND SITES ARE MINIMIZED.

THE CORE FUNDING CATEGORY WILL BE USED BY THE GROUND WATER QUALITY BUREAU (GWQB) TO FUND THE FOLLOWING ADMINISTRATIVE AND NON-SITE-SPECIFIC ACTIVITIES DURING THE GRANT PERIOD:
MIDDOT; PROGRAM MANAGEMENT, ADMINISTRATION AND PLANNING;
MIDDOT; FINANCIAL CLOSE OUT OF PREVIOUS SUPERFUND GRANTS;
MIDDOT; BUDGET PREPARATION/MANAGEMENT, PROCUREMENT AND LABOR ALLOCATIONS ACCOUNTING AND REPORTING SERVICES FOR NEW GRANT/PROPOSALS;
MIDDOT; STATE RECORDS AND ARCHIVES REPRESENTATION, COST RECOVERY RECORDS MAINTENANCE, AND COST RECOVERY REPORT PREPARATION;
MIDDOT; CONTRACT MANAGEMENT;
MIDDOT; INFORMATION TECHNOLOGY SUPPORT AND MAINTENANCE;
MIDDOT; CLERICAL SUPPORT; AND
MIDDOT; TRAINING FOR TECHNICAL STAFF.

SUBRECIPIENT:NO SUBAWARDS ARE INCLUDED IN THIS ASSISTANCE AGREEMENT.OUTCOMES:NMED PROPOSES TO COMPLETE THE EQUIVALENT OF THE FOLLOWING PRE-REMEDIAL OBJECTIVES PER YEAR DURING GRANT PERIOD: TWO PRE-CERCLASCREENING ASSESSMENTS; THREE PRELIMINARY ASSESSMENTS; AND FOUR SITE INSPECTIONS, SITE REASSESSMENTS, OR EXPANDED SITE INSPECTIONS. AT LEAST ONE NPL PACKAGE IS ANTICIPATED DURING THE GRANT PERIOD. ACTIVITIES PERFORMED DURING EACH PHASE OF WORK MAY INCLUDE, BUT ARE NOT LIMITED TO, THE FOLLOWING:
MIDDOT; COORDINATION AND COMMUNICATION WITH THE EPA SITE ASSESSMENT MANAGER (SAM) AND ENFORCEMENT STAFF;
MIDDOT; REVIEW OF AVAILABLE DOCUMENTS AND DATA;
MIDDOT; DEVELOPMENT OF SAMPLING PLANS AND RELATED SITE-SPECIFIC HEALTH AND SAFETY PLANS;
MIDDOT; COORDINATION AND COMMUNICATION WITH THE CONTRACT LABORATORY PROGRAM (CLP) OR HOUSTON LAB AND PREPARATION OF RESPECTIVE DOCUMENTS AND REQUESTS;
